<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-10-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-10-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="786" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-10-03"><hi rend="italic">October 3,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1.]</seg></opener>
                        <p>Our answer submitted to Spanish commissioners declining to join in
                            declarations as to restoration status quo in Philippine Islands on
                            rounds stated in our telegram October 1, well received by them. We then
                            submitted articles of the treaty covering Cuba, Puerto Rico, and other
                            islands in West Indies and Guam as provided in protocol. They asked
                            until Friday to consider them. Adjourned to Friday afternoon. Hear
                            Merritt to-morrow.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>